attributes.gcd: Refers to the unique identifier of the account or contract held by the customer. Account number is defined as numbers, letters or alphanumeric code assigned to every significant customer, supplier and lender for ease of reference in accounting records of the financial institution.
Refers to the date as on which the snapshot of source data extracted for processing.

Refers to the mantas classification associated with this record. This can be a jurisdiction which represents geographical or legal entity monitoring on data restrictions. Values can be AMEA, INDV, CORP etc.

Refers to the source system from where data is extracted. Data can be sourced from multiple sources, this column will Refers to the source code from where the data is extracted for this extraction date.
Refers to the type of application assessment for which this identification document has provided. For example, KYC or FATCA i.e. Foreign Account Tax Compliance Act.
Refers to the expiry date of the document received from party.
Refers to the unique identifier of the document submitted.
Refers to the issuing date of the document received from party.
Refers to the issuing authority of the document received from party.
Refers to the name of the received document. For example, PAN Card, Passport, etc.

Refers to the purpose of the document submitted. For CRS purposes this field will capture the NO TIN reason codes.
List of reason code is as below.
IRAS101: Pre-existing Account. IN is not available. No TIN reason code for CRS reporting Singapore template specific.
IRAS102: New Account. Residence Jurisdiction does not issue IN. No TIN reason code for CRS reporting Singapore template specific.
IRAS103: New Account. Residence Jurisdiction does not require IN to be reported. No TIN reason code for CRS reporting Singapore template specific.
IRAS104: New Account, with reasonable explanation and documentation on the absence of IN. No TIN reason code for CRS reporting Singapore template specific.
CA1: The account holder will apply or has applied for a TIN but has not yet received it. No TIN reason code for CRS reporting Canada template specific.
CA2: The account holderâ€™s jurisdiction of tax residence does not issue TINs to its residents. No TIN reason code for CRS reporting Canada template specific.
CA3: Other reason. No TIN reason code for CRS reporting Canada template specific.

Refers to the party submits financial and identity documents to the financial institution as part of the KYC Verification or Covenants which is periodic basis. The document reference number uniquely identifies the document submitted by the party.
Refers to the document status. Possible List of valid values are Provided, Will Provide Later, Not Providing.
Refers to the Description or reason that further explains the document Status.
Refers to the document sub type. Sample values are like if the document type is visa then the sub type will be student or tourist visa.
Flag indicates whether any official documentation has been issued by an authorized government body for this party. List of values are Y, N. Y is yes, N is no.

Refers to the country code associated with the business. There are several popular country codes as part of ISO 3166 standard published by the International Organization for Standardization. ISO 3166 defines codes for the names of countries, dependent territories, special areas of geographical interest and their principal subdivisions. In case of party, it Refers to the country of birth of the party.

Refers to the code of the type of the document submitted. List of valid values are ART is Registered articles of incorporation, BC is Certificate of Birth, BL is Business License, BR is Report of Birth Abroad, BS is Bank Statement, CC is Cancelled Check, CIC is Certificate of Citizenship, CID is Citizen Identification Card, CO is Court Order for Name Change or Gender Change or Adoption or Divorce, DPS is Domestic Passport, EMP is Employment Authorization Card, FPS is Foreign Passport with Appropriate Immigration Documents, IDV is IDV, LS is Legal Structure Documents, MC is Marriage Certificate, MD is Mortgage Documents, MIL is Military Identification Card, News Search is News Search, NTR is Certificate of Naturalization, PA is Partnership Agreement, PC is Paycheck Stub with Name or Address, PIV is Personal Identity Verification Card, PRES is Permanent Resident Alien Card, Qualified is Qualified, RTD is Unexpired Refugee Travel Document, SS is Social Security Card, TI is Trust Instruments, TRES is Temporary Resident Identification Card, UB is Utility Bill Address, USTD is U.S. Tribal or Bureau of Indian Affairs Identification Card, VR is Vehicle Registration Card or Title, VRC is Voters Registration Card, Watch List is Watch List, Firm specified is Other values as specified by the client.
Refers to the customer identity verification performed manually or by system. If it is by system, it needs to provide the external source system name who has performed the verification.

attributes.logicalName: Party Identification Programme Verification Status Code
attributes.gcd: Refers to the status of the identification verification performed in the system.
Refers to the user of the source system who has verified the identification process.
Refers to the unique identifier for the party. Party is defined as an entity or a person who takes part or is involved in an agreement, lawsuit, or transaction.

Flag indicates that the party submitted the corresponding document as his or her primary document. There can be more than one document getting submitted by party. This flag identifies the primary document. List of values are Y, N. If Y, the document is primary document and if N, the document is not primary document.
Refers to the record creation date. It has been added to all catalog entities to enable partitioning and archival.
Refers to the run identifier for a set of Records participating in the particular Run with the Run Execution identifier. This is a combination of Run Main Identifier and Run Execution Identifier.

Flag indicates if the party is considered a resident of the jurisdiction for Govt ID. Nation is used to indicate if the party is a tax resident of the indicated country, Jurisdiction to indicate if the party is a tax resident of a particular country. List of values are Y, N.
